The administration and inspection requirements of this subchapter shall be the responsibility of the Building Official. The
Building Official shall determine compliance with this subchapter prior to the approval or the issuance of a building permit.
(Ord. 08-347, passed - -2008)
§ 155.126 EXCEPTIONS TO OFF-STREET PARKING REQUIREMENTS.
(A) The Building Official is granted the authority to issue a building permit where there are minor discrepancies with
regard to the requirements established in this subchapter, where it is determined that the literal application of the
requirements would constitute an undue hardship with regard to the applicant's particular circumstances and would not be
essential in accomplishing the objectives of this subchapter.
(B) In areas that are fully or near fully developed, a variance of up to 30% of the number of off-street parking spaces
required in this subchapter shall be allowed by the Building Official, if the conversion of a structure from a nonresidential use
to another use would require the addition of more off-street parking, and if it is determined that the literal application of the
revisions would constitute an undue hardship with regard to the applicant's particular circumstances and would not be
essential in accomplishing the objectives of this subchapter.
(C) If the applicant is dissatisfied with the decision of the Building Official with regard to a requested exception, the
applicant shall be entitled to appeal the decision to the Board.
(D) The off-street parking requirements of this chapter will not apply to buildings and uses in the 400 Block of Main
Street.
(Ord. 08-347, passed - -2008; Ord. 2013-08-20-1, passed 8-20-2013)
§ 155.127 MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS FOR SPACES.
There shall be provided, at a time as a building permit is issued for the erection, alteration or use change of a structure,
off-street parking spaces in accordance with the following minimum requirements:
(A) Bowling alley: five parking spaces for each lane;
(B) Business or professional office, studio, bank, medical or dental clinic: three parking spaces plus one additional
parking space for each 250 square feet of floor area over 500;
(C) Church, theater, auditorium (except school), sports arena, stadium or gymnasium: one parking space for each four
seats or bench seating spaces;
(D) Library, museum or art gallery: ten parking spaces plus one additional space for each 300 square feet of floor area in
excess of 2,000 square feet. If an auditorium is included as a part of the building, its floor area shall be deducted from the
total and additional parking provided on the basis of one space for each four seats that it contains;
(E) Dance hall, assembly or exhibition hall without fixed seats: one parking space for each 100 square feet of floor area
used thereof;
(F) Fraternity, sorority or dormitory: one parking space for each bed;
(G) Furniture or appliance store, hardware store, wholesale establishment, machinery or equipment sales and service,
clothing or shoe repair or service shop: one parking space for each 300 square feet of floor area;
(H) Hospital: four parking spaces plus one additional parking space for each four beds;
(I) Hotel: one parking space for each sleeping room or suite plus one space for each 200 square feet of commercial floor
area contained therein;
(J) Industrial plant: the number of parking spaces required to accommodate all plant employees and construction forces
on any single shift;
(K) Mortuary or funeral home: one parking space for each 50 square feet of floor space in slumber rooms, parlors or
individual funeral service rooms;
(L) Motor vehicle sales room and used car lot: one parking space for each 800 square feet of sales floor or lot area;
(M) Private club, lodge, country club or golf club: one parking space for each 150 square feet of floor area or for every
five members, whichever is greater;
(N) Restaurant, nightclub, café or similar recreation or amusement establishment: one parking space for each 100
square feet of floor area;
(O) Retail store or personal service establishment, except as otherwise specified in this section: one parking space for
each 250 square feet of retail sales or floor area;
(P) Rooming house or boardinghouse: one parking space for each sleeping room;
(Q) Sanitarium, convalescent home, home for the aged or similar institution: one parking space for each six beds;
